  "suggestion": "Life is locally too expensive — each organism spends 3-4x the energy it should. Space underutilization compounds beauty. Rewire for efficient wandering + active exploration.; Efficiency (0.465) is the critical bottleneck — ~40% gap from other metrics. Organisms burn energy on movement/pulsing relative to survival gain. Secondary: spatialComposition (0.3) and diversityOfForms (0.474) indicate organisms cluster instead of spreading. Solution: (1) Reduce active energy costs (moveSpeed, pulseFrequency, swimStrength down), increase drag to 0.98+ for smoother motion; (2) boost avoidanceRadius and explorationDrive to scatter organisms and encourage different growth strategies; (3) organism 2 thrives (26 energy) while others struggle (5-7) — indicates genotype-specific energy requirements. Jellyfish should reduce resource attraction, crawler should increase it.",
